RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 1 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 56. Claiming Purse 11000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PEACEFUL MOMENT vied for the lead, was pressured by an outside contender, backed off and stalked from the rail, drew next to the early pace setter after the half mile pole, launched a bid at the three eighths pole, pulled away and led by a length into the stretch drive, maintained the lead through out and willingly got the win. SHEZA CAT was off a step slow, settled off of the pace, raced on the rail and saved ground, edged out at the five sixteenth pole into the three path, responded well to urging and willing closed, passed other rivals by the quarter pole but chased the leader down the stretch, could not catch the eventual winner but was second best. ZEEROCK was off of the pace and raced on the rail, settled and found his stride, made one run up the rail, saving ground and improving with every stride, passed along the rail through the turn, and finished closing up the rail for a well earned third. ROSALIE'S DESTINY raced in the four path, moved at the half mile pole, launched a bid at the three eighths pole, circled the field in the five path, responded to urging and closed. OAK HILL SENIORITA stalked the early pace from the three path, then faded after the three eighths pole. WATCH OUT NOW vied for the lead, raced in the two path, set the pace, was pressured from an inside contender, was joined on the inside by the eventual winner, faded after the five sixteenth pole. JAGO was off a step slow, angled out into the four path in the first turn, raced on the outside down the back side, and faded after the half mile pole. ICONIC BONNET raced on the rail, went wrong, vanned off. ICONIC BONNET WENT WRONG AND WAS PULLED UP AND VANNED OFF.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 2 5F Dirt CR: 52. Maiden Claiming Purse 18000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000. (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at Five Furlongs) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHEWASN'TEASY vied for the early lead, matched strides with another determined rival for the lead, settled just off of the lead, took advantage of the inside post and raced on the rail, drew next to the other front runner moving into the turn, matched strides and entered the stretch together as a set, battled down the lane, in hands and lightly encouraged, were together nose to nose, then in the last four jumps SHEWASN'TEASY was cued and responded by drawing off and winning easily. TRIPLE THE GOLD vied for the lead, had to match strides and battle with an inside foe, finally got a break from the inside challenger and led while being pressured, was joined on the inside at the three eighth s pole, matched strides through the turn, entered the stretch together and battled down the lane, was in stride with the inside rival and racing well then in the last few jumps was left behind and chased the eventual winner to the wire just missing for the win. LUYV had an awkward break, was quickly corrected, raced in the three path and stalked the front runners, was well placed and driven into the stretch, was kept on point and continued to closed ground out finishing the rest of the field, and getting up for third. LONG SHOT LOUISE raced from mid pack on the rail, saved ground, and maintained that position throughout. BRIELLE EVANGELINE had an awkward start, gathered herself up, found her stride, made one run along the out side in the four path, circled the field through the turn, closed well down the stretch. JENNYSBIGBABY had an awkward start, raced in the four path from mid pack, raced even. SHE'S WAYNE'S was off a step slow, raced on the rail with another rival to her outside but had no impact. JESSOLOGY was off a step slow, raced in a set on the outside in the three path and was never involved.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 3 5F Dirt CR: 57. Maiden Claiming Purse 10000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MISS CHARGE IT raced on the rail, stalked the pace, angled out into the four path in the upper stretch, closed under urging, cleared the front runners at the sixteenth pole and drew off for the win. GLITZ AND GLAMOUR raced in the two path, vied for the lead, matched with another competitor, finally got the lead, led and set the pace briefly, was joined by an inside determined rival and jointly set the fractions, matched strides wit this one until the eighth pole, drifted out a bit in the furlong ground, was cleared by a fast closing outside contender and went on to finished in the place spot. E R'S MIREYA vied for the lead, battled with another determined rival to lead, led as a set matching strides, raced on the rai through out, entered the stretch and battled for the first sixteenth with the same rival then gave way after the eighth pole. THE X FACTOR was off a bit slow, raced mid pack and in the four path, made one run, angled out into the nine path in the upper stretch and closed. SENSING GOLD raced mid pack and in the three path, raced giving an even effort. SWEET N SALTY stalked from the three path, raced on the outside of the second flight, stopped after the quarter pole. BEAUCLAIRE raced in the two path, stalked from in between to rivals in the second flight, shuffled back at the quarter pole, finished flat. BABY YOUR PERFECT raced on the rail, trailed through out and was never involved. OUR HALLIE missed the break and showed little. WA WA WEE WA raced from off of the pace, three wide and had no impact.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 4 7F Dirt CR: 83. Claiming Purse 13000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MINT was able to make the front and take the rail with out too much effort, settled next to another contender and set the pace as a set, happily matched strides and raced with company until he launched a bid at the three eighths pole and drew away, put about a length between himself and the field, raced down the stretch under encouragement on the rail, was able t hold on for the win. STANS HOME RUN raced four wide and stalked the early leaders, circled the field in the turn, closed down the lane in the four path, caughta tiring front runner at the eighth pole, cleared that one, but could not catch the winner and was second best today. HAIL SOUTHERN vied for the lead, raced in the two path, set the fractions in company with the eventual winner, tired after the eighth pole but had done enough work early was still able to claim third place rewards. BREW CREW raced in the three path between foes in the third flight of horses, improved position slowly gaining ground, raced in the two path in the upper stretch and closed mildly. QUICK TO BLAME raced five wide, from mid pack and maintained that position through out. LEMON KICK was mid pack, raced in the three path in the third flight of horses, had no impact. AFRICAN WARRIOR stalked the early pace from the three path, circled the field in the turn then tired in the stretch. SHANGHAI'S DREAM raced five wide, from off of the pace and had no kick. MIND ON MY MONEY raced on the rail, was in mid pack early, saved ground but to no avail. SWEET RACHEL was never involved. ROBTADI STORM showed little.

(If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at 1 1/16 Miles) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MR. TIN MAN led, had pressure through out, battled in between foes in the stretch shook the one to the outside, battled to the wire with and determinedly got his nose in front. THROWIN' SHADE stalked the leader from the rail, launched a bid at the quarter pole, battled in a three way battle, shook one then went on to the wire, trading punches, all the way and just missed. A MILLION STARS raced on the rail, saved ground, launched a mild bid late. KINGS WAGER raced three wide, was in the middle of the pack, then faded. HALF A BUCK raced in the four path but was never involved. PAYNTED LOVER trailed through out.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 6 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 93. Allowance Purse 29000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since June 9 Allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $20,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NAMESAKE vied for the lead in the two path, shifted into the three path through the turn, lost ground in the turn, was driven down the stretch, come back and closed, caught the leader at the eighth pole, had the momentum and passed this rival for the lead and was able to hold sway. DINNER AT CRUMPIES vied for the lead, raced in the two path, stalked the early leader, relaxed for a few strides, saved ground in the turn was asked and responded willingly closing with every stride down the lane and getting up for a game second. EFFICIENCY raced in the three path, stalked the early leader, raced from in between rivals, shifted out six wide into the upper stretch and closed on the outside gaining third place. KID SHELLEEN raced in the two path, stalked the pace, advanced and moved in between horses, was in contention and finished even. PHANTOM RIDE vied for the lead, raced on the rail while setting the early pace and then faltered late. CHIEF CHEETAH was off a bit slow, launched a mild bid late. BUTLER CABIN was on the outside of the second tier of horses, raced in the five path, shifted into the six path in the upper stretch but had no late kick. BIG SUCCESS showed little.
